As much as I hate to give two stars..".. Food was amazing. Had the Blueberry Pancakes and Banana bread French toast. Very fresh and great flavor.  Staff was very friendly but they were non existent. They were not very busy and we waited for at least 10 minutes before someone even came over to seat us. Once seated it was another 10 minutes before our waitress came over. I was watching the whole time as I’m a people watcher. All the waitresses seemed to be in the kitchen 90%of the time. Unless they are having them cook I don’t understand. We watched other people come in and not be acknowledged and wait for 15 minutes and left. Then when they were seated it took forever for them to get serviced. You could see the frustration. They seemed to be decently staffed but they need to figure out why they are in the kitchen all the time. We had to ask the girl that was clearing tables to get our check. She got it and I was surprised our waitress didn’t bring it out. Again they were nit that busy. I appreciated that she brought it so fast and gave her $5 for her help. Our waitress finally came out as we were leaving and said Thank You. We really enjoyed our visit but thinking we will skip Caroline’s.

Oh my food goodness! Best dish I have had in Dubuque. Roasted Spaghetti Squash is full of amazing fresh flavors. The tomatoes exploded with fresh flavor and the mushrooms are the right amount of firmness. I asked them to add grilled chicken for more protein. Great Job!

I wish we could have received an explanation at some point because I cannot even imagine what was going wrong and why!  No explanation, no attempts to remedy, no desire to return.

The two stars are for the atmosphere of the restaurant. Everything was incredibly overpriced, we had bad service and our experience was not great. We were very excited to come here for date night, as we noticed this restaurant right after we moved to Dubuque and we're very excited to have a nice night out. However, our service was very slow, and we felt as though our server was rude towards our feelings, questions and requests that we made. We felt as though we became an afterthought to our server after it took about 15 minutes for her to come back after we said we needed a little more time to look at the menu and took her quite some time after the food came to check on how it was. I loved my dinner and had originally wanted to substitute something else for asparagus as I do not like it, the waitress said we do not do salads after I asked if I could substitute for a side salad, and she said " I'm not quite sure what you are asking" , and looked at me with a blank stare. My wife and I have been in the service industry for quite a long time and we've never been treated that way as a customer, and would never treat one of our customers the way my wife and I were treated this evening. Instead of doing everything that could have been done to help us feel better and make us happy, we felt like we were being brushed off and we just wanted to leave as soon as possible. My wife ordered the special for the evening and it turned out to be what felt like an entire box of pasta drenched in olive oil with a few tomatoes, olives, overcooked shrimp and feta cheese sprinkled on top... We do not feel like a bowl of pasta salad that has been warmed up should not be $22. Overall we were incredibly disappointed and upset with how our nice date night came to fruition. What we thought was going to be a new place for us to go for special occasions and night out with friends will now be on our list of places we will not go and will tell people we had a bad experience.

What a sad, sad, disappointment. Hubby took me here for a celebratory dinner. I was so so excited. I remember coming at one point to this restaurant and I was in awe. So , I knew what to expect. Or rather, I thought I knew. To make things shorter, cuz I could right a novel, our waitress was not attentive at all. I had to ask her to bring out the bread for us. My meal was really bad- I got "half a chicken" and it wasn't even a 1/4th. I got 3 dinky pieces and they weren't even that well done, but I had nobody to turn too because our waitress was now up a floor doing God know's what. When we finally got our bill we waited for her and nothing. so I've finally had enough to went to the bar to pay.Of course one girl was lolling around, the other went to take care of it and five minutes later comes back to tell us "You're waitress will be taking care of it in a minute". Are you serious? Give me back my $66 dollars I paid.

Came in on a quiet Friday night. There were 3 tables total with people at them, a few at the bar and 2 servers that I could see. It still ended up taking over 20 min for our server to bring our drinks, and another 15 before she came back for our order. Overall terrible service with a server who couldn't answer any questions about the food, we heard the next table from ours complain about the same thing to the manager, who then purposely avoided coming to our table (she rushed by and in passing asked if everything was ok. "Good? Good.")  And then the food - horrible for the price. We were expecting a great meal based on the descriptions and expense. I've never had such dry, tasteless pork. (Although my friends prime rib was not bad). Had the manager stopped by I would have sent my food back for the first time ever. As it was we were sick of waiting for the server to check on us and just wanted to get out of there. Went elsewhere for dessert because I was still hungry! Won't be going back, obviously.

Failed to meet expectations. Good food, but not as good as the price would suggest. Morning omelette was overdone and served with dry ham chunks. Dinner was a tenderloin and smashed potatos. Far too much salt, on everything. Steak ordered medium rare, arrived med. well. Nice and juicy, tender and flavorful cut. Asked for Maker's bourbon in my drink, got Jack Daniel's. $30 for a fairly small serving of steak and potatoes-- and $6 extra to split it.

I am in complete awe of the lack of professionalism behind the hostess stand this morning. I was placed awkwardly right in front of it to eat, and couldn't help but overhear. Customers consistently came in and were told their reservations were "messed up" because "she" decided to give their tables away. The "she" was apparently the manager who the employee had no problem telling customers about and spoke poorly of - repeatedly!! Just in complete shock that this type of behavior and disrespect could be tolerated.

The items that are fresh made are wonderful. I had the shrimp Thai noodles and could eat it every day. But there were some items that weren't made fresh, like their cinnamon rolls. It looked and tasted like something that had been nuked from a frozen state. I'd eat here again but only for their dinner menu.

Ummmm .... Uneven.  When I walked into restaurant,  someone did come out and greet me - in a rather off hand way. I asked if the restaurant was open. Once I checked my watch and confirmed for the server that it was indeed after 4:30 ....I was seated.  Sigh.  I ordered the short ribs and soup of the day. Fresh warm bread was served with olive oil - at least a third of a cup of olive oil. At least. I'm eating alone.  Really? How much olive oil do people use?  The soup of the day was cheeseburger. I thought it would be interesting. It sort of was. Not in a good way. It tasted like a cheeseburger, but not a particularly good one. I'm willing to admit, maybe it was just me. Someone else might love it.  Short ribs were quite good. The fingerling potatoes were unremarkable and tasteless. I guess I could have dunked them in the excess olive oil. Yuck.  My bill got dropped off. I proffered my credit card. It was run. Then returned .... With no pen. I could have used my blood .... Or the olive oil .... Took a while to get a pen. Sigh.  It was an experience.

On 10/15 four of us arrived as the restaurant was opening. We each ordered a steak and the menu said they each came with smashed potatoes and broccolini. When asked the waitress said broccolini is broccoli with the stem still attached and is more bitter than broccoli. Gee, who could resist such a delicacy as bitter broccoli. We then asked about substituting a different vegetable that was at the same price as the broccolini and were told there would be an "up-charge" of the full price of another side to substitute. The waitress was asked about substituting french fries for the smashed potatoes and you guessed it, there would be an up-charge for that.  We were there for 2.5 hrs, had a meal of mediocre steaks, broccolini that none of us wanted or ate and extremely slow service. There are many places in Dubuque that will give you better service, better choices on their menu and better prices for similar meals.

Caroline's is a wonderful restaurant. Dinner is elegant and relaxed with warm, welcoming staff. We had the ribeye and the shrimp feature per our server's recommendation. Go to the Hotel Julien website for a current menu as we were told some of the items mentioned here haven't been served for years!

We were driving through and saw that this restaurant had high ratings so we tried it out. It's a very plush restaurant and we were dressed casually and they still treated us like royalty. We had the salmon (excellent!), the tortellini (rich and delicious), and the burger (wonderful). The milk bread is to die for and I would love to track down that recipe. The soup was amazing also. The food is worth the price! If we are ever back to Dubuque we will come back!
I'll easily agree with most of the other folks on this post!  Very good food, very good service, nice looking place, good parking.  I'm looking forward to my next trip.  Enjoy!

We ordered room service while staying at the Julien. The food was very bland and they sent the wrong side and salads with the meal. For a $30 plate of seafood pasta I expected more flavor and taste. In addition they charged a room delivery fee on top of 20% gratuity in the bill. Considering the food and incorrect order I would not have been that generous. A little presumptious on their behalf.
